Each class starts out with a group warm-up, followed by a fast-paced workout and concludes with a cool-down. You will work hard, learn usable skills, have fun and get results.

Saturday, August 31.event_name: Free Concert - St. Paul and the Broken Bones
Saturday, August 31.short_description: St. Paul and the Broken Bones
Saturday, August 31.long_description:
No tickets are required for this FREE concert produced by CDDC & Capitol South.

Bar and food trucks will open at 5:30pm. Music begins with local legends The Spikedrivers with St. Paul and The Broken Bones to follow.

Blankets and chairs are welcome; please leave coolers at home. Beverage sales and food trucks are available on site.

Convenient parking is available at the Columbus Commons Garages, located at 191 S. Third St. and 55 E. Rich St.

Sunday, September 1.long_description:
Lawn chairs and blankets are welcome, please leave coolers at home. Easy and convenient parking is available just south of the park at the Columbus Commons Main Garage, located at 55 East Rich Street.

Bars and food trucks open at 6 pm; music begins at 8 pm.

For more information, click here!
